
plain text files with no identifying extension will be processed through a series
of filters to identify any data that matches a format as well as pull out tags,
keys and properties.

- tags are self identified based on format and similar to the value of a property
- keys are system identified and provide some identity without  a special value
- properties are system defined keys with a value, though the value maybe true or
    false and may be specified by the presence of the key ( in which case lack
    of presence means undefined not false )

text processing can be done in a custom session that handles all initial text files
